wlc_get_outputs(3)                                     WLC OUTPUT API FUNCTIONS

NAME

    wlc_get_outputs - get list of outputs

SYNOPSIS

    #include <wlc/wlc.h>

    const wlc_handle* wlc_get_outputs(size_t *out_count);

DESCRIPTION

    wlc_get_outputs() is used to return an array of wlc_handles while setting
    the out_count parameter to the number of outputs available.

RETURN VALUE

    wlc_get_outputs() returns an array of wlc_handles.

NOTES

    The returned array is a direct reference so care is needed when moving and
    destroying handles.  If ownership is required the array should be copied
    instead.

EXAMPLE

    #include <wlc/wlc.h>

    size_t count;
    const wlc_handle *outputs = wlc_get_outputs(&count);

    for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i)
        wake_up(outputs[i]);
